This paper deals with the lambda calculus and its extension, the lambda-value calculus, which are both topics in mathematical logic and theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses proof-theory and equational reasoning, which are also relevant to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.TL (Theoretical Computer Science). The paper also touches on the concept of operational relevance, which is related to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata). Finally, the paper includes a proof of the Genericity Lemma, which is a result in model theory and is relevant to cs.LG (Logic in Computer Science).
